verbose_text: It has been shown that Akt1 / PKBalpha undergoes transient phosphorylation / dephosphorylation which regulates the kinase active conformation cycle; kinase disulfide bond formation, Cys 297 -Cys 311, and dephosphorylation at pThr 308 are induced simultaneously by H 2 O 2 oxidative stress in vitro; and high levels of nitric oxide production occurs in both burn injured rats and diabetic patients.
